My Meme

My meme describes the inevitable pain of someone when theyve found out the truth of a sugar coated lie, this meme captures this as I added new text above the screaming women (representing the victim of the lie) and the cat (the sugar coater).

Here is my meme, cats really do run the world

library(magick)

#square one (LA)
la_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                          height = 150,
                          color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "You said we were going to LA",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 35,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

la_text


#square two (screaming women)
screaming_women <- image_read("https://github.com/francescamd/stats220/blob/main/Women.jpg?raw=true") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#square three (Lower Auckland)
lowerakl_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                       height = 150,
                       color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Lower  Auckland",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Palatino",
                 gravity = "center")

#square four (cat)
cat <- image_read("https://github.com/francescamd/stats220/blob/main/Cat.jpg?raw=true") %>%
  image_scale(506)

# appending text boxes
top_row <- image_append(c(la_text, lowerakl_text))

# appending images
bottom_row <- image_append(c(screaming_women, cat))


# adding it all together
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)%>%
  # saving meme as png
  image_write("my_meme.png", format= "png" )

My Animation

My gif shows the process of an ice cream being munched, I edited each frame individually using Canva and then animated them together.

Here is my meme, I wish I could eat ice cream in class

library(magick)

# naming images as frames
frame1 <- image_read("1.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#9342f5", font = 'serif')

# make them rotate to smaller and smaller 
frame2 <- image_read("2.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#42f5ad", font = 'serif')

frame3 <- image_read("3.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#42f5e0", font = 'serif')

frame4 <- image_read("4.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#4287f5", font = 'serif')


frame5 <- image_read("5.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#9342f5", font = 'serif')

frame6 <- image_read("6.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#f542d4", font = 'serif')

frame7 <- image_read("7.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#f54269", font = 'serif')

frame8 <- image_read("8.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#f58d42", font = 'serif')

frame9 <- image_read("9.png")%>%
  image_annotate("Tastes like SUMMER", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "#4287f5", font = 'serif')

# creating frames as a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5, frame6, frame7, frame8, frame9)%>%
  #making them all the same size
  image_scale(450)


# adding it all together
frames %>%
  image_animate(fps = 2)%>%
  # saving animation as gif
  image_write("my_animation.gif", format= "gif" )
